fir
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number: 3
Definition:Once used in many places in NZ, popularly and indiscriminately, for <i>Pinus</i> sp, esp. <i>P. radiata</i> (formerly <i>insignis</i>; by the 1960s an old-fashioned solecism, since pine trees and timber have become common, and commonly known.


